ConnectorDefinition.name: SingleStore
ConnectorDefinition.description: SingleStore connector allows Informatica to connect to SingleStoreDB and SingleStore Managed Service, to allow transfer and integration of data between SingleStore databases and other sources and targets supported by Informatica.

ConnectionAttribute.name: hostname
ConnectionAttribute.description: An IP address or DNS name of the SingleStoreDB Aggregator or SingleStoreDB Cloud workspace to run queries against

ConnectionAttribute.name: port
ConnectionAttribute.description: Port of the SingleStoreDB Aggregator or SingleStoreDB Cloud workspace to run queries against

ConnectionAttribute.name: database
ConnectionAttribute.description: If set, all connections will default to using this database

ConnectionAttribute.name: password
ConnectionAttribute.description: The password of the database user

ConnectionAttribute.name: useSsl
ConnectionAttribute.description: Force enables SSL/TLS on the connection.

ConnectionAttribute.name: serverSslCert
ConnectionAttribute.description: Use this parameter to specify the server's certificate in DER format or specify the server's CA certificate. You can specify the server certificate in one of the following formats: complete path (/full_path/cert.pem), relative path (classpath:relative/cert.pem), DER-encoded certificate (------BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----...)

ConnectionAttribute.name: keyStore
ConnectionAttribute.description: Specifies the path of the Key Store file that contains the client private keys and associated certificates

ConnectionAttribute.name: keyStorePassword
ConnectionAttribute.description: Specifies the password for the Key Store file

ConnectionAttribute.name: keyPassword
ConnectionAttribute.description: Specifies the password for the private key in the client certificate file (Key Store))

ConnectionAttribute.name: trustStore
ConnectionAttribute.description: Specifies the path of the Trust Store file, and uses the specified file for trusted root certificates. If this parameter is set, it overrides the Server SSL Certificate parameter

ConnectionAttribute.name: trustStorePassword
ConnectionAttribute.description: Specifies the password for the trusted root certificate file.

ConnectionAttribute.name: trustServerCertificate
ConnectionAttribute.description: Enable this parameter to skip checking the server's certificate when used in conjunction with SSL/TLS

ConnectionAttribute.name: disableSslHostnameVerification
ConnectionAttribute.description: Disables hostname verification against the server's identity as specified in the server's certificate to prevent man-in-the-middle attacks.
